Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell[TextData[{
 "2",
 StyleBox[" | Variational Quantum Eigensolver (VQE)", "SectionBar"]
}], "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.652728456208679*^9, 3.652728527108994*^9, 3.9660937117300777`*^9, {
   3.966343289083021*^9, 3.966343302001837*^9}},
 CounterAssignments->{{"Section", 0}},
 CellID->172133015,ExpressionUUID->"a2ad295c-ee47-ba43-9362-53650d3de16a"],

Cell["\<\
Here is the core question of this chapter: given a quantum system described \
by a Hamiltonian, what is its lowest-energy state? Classical computers can \
answer this for small molecules, but the Hilbert space grows exponentially \
with particle number, and no classical data structure can represent the full \
quantum state efficiently. A quantum computer, by contrast, lives in exactly \
the kind of exponentially large Hilbert space that defeats classical \
simulation. VQE exploits this: the quantum hardware prepares and measures \
trial states, while a classical optimizer navigates the parameter landscape \
toward the ground state. This hybrid structure is not a compromise, it is a \
design choice matched to near-term quantum hardware, where circuits must be \
short and noise is unavoidable.\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->675048279,ExpressionUUID->"e85d3d40-9885-b848-818d-45eb219aa652"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Physical Background", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803387801733704`*^9, 3.9803387887494926`*^9}},
 CellID->43360156,ExpressionUUID->"f1ff79af-831a-fe4a-ad97-9e41e68d0f91"],

Cell["\<\
VQE computes ground-state energies of quantum systems especially molecules. \
To understand the algorithm, we first need the central object of quantum \
physics: the Hamiltonian.\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->135589924,ExpressionUUID->"f69de90b-7bbc-4a4c-929d-80cb4617056f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["What is a Hamiltonian?", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.980338833016472*^9},
 CellID->324808347,ExpressionUUID->"7d79ec5e-b1f5-c44e-bbd3-78694114572f"],

Cell["\<\
In classical mechanics, a system evolves according to \
Newton\[CloseCurlyQuote]s laws, or equivalently, through Hamilton\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s equations. In quantum mechanics, a single object plays \
both roles: encoding the energy and generating the dynamics. This is the \
Hamiltonian. Physically, it is the energy operator. It contains every piece \
of physics:\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->54907258,ExpressionUUID->"012dd012-8ae5-9748-ac45-71e9d028768e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Kinetic energy\t", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980338911778656*^9, 3.980338930866457*^9}},
 CellID->381275342,ExpressionUUID->"0027af74-e750-ec4c-bf92-69afe1ef7665"],

Cell["Potential energy", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803389195554066`*^9, 3.9803389230230427`*^9}},
 CellID->23614600,ExpressionUUID->"d71233f3-7967-7f46-ae65-f79baa5fccd6"],

Cell["Interactions between particles", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803389418969727`*^9, 3.9803389464184265`*^9}},
 CellID->163778187,ExpressionUUID->"f964c61b-77e8-ad42-a613-e9e611005e85"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
If you know the Hamiltonian, you know the system.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980338842156893*^9, 3.980338950239382*^9}},
 CellID->183138110,ExpressionUUID->"4a7d3b99-588d-084f-95d6-d630fa4ecfcf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Mathematically, the Hamiltonian is an operator ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["\|01d43b", "^"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cc043532-d03d-7b43-b4c4-6903b7dfd0b4"],
 " that acts on quantum states. The central equation is the time-independent \
Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation:"
}], "Text",
 CellID->636024929,ExpressionUUID->"ce8cb3c6-0eee-4345-ac74-1bef31e1f774"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       OverscriptBox["H", "^"], 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "E"]},
        "Ket"]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{"E", 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "E"]},
        "Ket"]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"e206a794-bf03-8349-b035-04456f1274ea"]], \
"Text",
 CellID->85890015,ExpressionUUID->"a8b7af7f-817e-0044-afb2-118f4575b6f9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is an eigenvalue equation. Here ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["E", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "9a13b768-f2ba-48b8-85a0-6765b22dd7f0"],
 " is the eigenvalue (the allowed energy) and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "E"]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9808d1dc-c6c7-45dd-b6d3-efc0d680c40e"],
 " is the corresponding eigenstate. The physical content:"
}], "Text",
 CellID->41529473,ExpressionUUID->"d9c0e014-10a4-1140-84cb-63d11c4a7a59"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
The allowed energies are the eigenvalues of the Hamiltonian.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393669812756`*^9, 3.9803393704670506`*^9}},
 CellID->129867076,ExpressionUUID->"2c5d847f-bea9-d742-84a5-43c342307b0a"],

Cell["The corresponding quantum states are its eigenvectors.", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393669812756`*^9, 3.98033937112661*^9}},
 CellID->29428035,ExpressionUUID->"e17f8d81-e8af-5d49-8ae8-801e1e011591"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["The goal of VQE:", "Text",
 CellID->91048427,ExpressionUUID->"e5c8495d-a6ce-0e4e-b5eb-455034ae90a5"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Given a Hamiltonian, find its lowest eigenvalue (the \
ground-state energy).",
 FontSlant->"Italic"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9803397095400295`*^9},
 TextAlignment->Center,
 CellID->563494885,ExpressionUUID->"293ea22a-7e7c-ed4d-95f6-5c7f33a98c47"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Why Molecular Energies Are Hard", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980342715947233*^9, 3.980342718003765*^9}, {
  3.980343156770548*^9, 3.980343156777611*^9}},
 CellID->1634723,ExpressionUUID->"1909a1d3-1d70-1342-9ef5-227af905c2f4"],

Cell["\<\
A molecule consists of nuclei (heavy, positively charged) and electrons \
(light, negatively charged). Every particle interacts with every other \
through Coulomb forces. The total Hamiltonian includes:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980342710901764*^9, 3.980342757550621*^9}, 
   3.980343146217346*^9},
 CellID->289779811,ExpressionUUID->"59ba324a-4191-744b-9543-d3197e6bf8a9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Kinetic energy of nuclei", "Item",
 CellID->87966558,ExpressionUUID->"4a684a83-d082-5840-9907-11c5a9988605"],

Cell["Kinetic energy of electrons", "Item",
 CellID->47298800,ExpressionUUID->"3a5532b0-e15c-ca4e-8ee6-dc75bc92bf48"],

Cell["Electron\[Dash]nucleus attraction", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803427618402233`*^9, 3.9803428169259815`*^9}},
 CellID->18833898,ExpressionUUID->"0142267c-4a67-634e-b542-f25186fa993e"],

Cell["Electron\[Dash]electron repulsion", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803427618402233`*^9, 3.980342814590662*^9}},
 CellID->127455417,ExpressionUUID->"1bdb11d9-c99a-ae48-8296-08e31afba71c"],

Cell["Nucleus\[Dash]nucleus repulsion", "Item",
 CellID->597443251,ExpressionUUID->"f41367d6-7132-4344-becd-f7dfe1274408"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Even for a small molecule, this is an enormous many-body problem. The full \
molecular Schr\[ODoubleDot]dinger equation reads:\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->254825790,ExpressionUUID->"702a5f83-b225-2c42-b377-44f31f6a5099"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["H", "^"], "molecular"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["\[Psi]",
         FontWeight->"Bold"], "(", 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], ",", 
         StyleBox["R",
          FontWeight->"Bold"]}], ")"}]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["E", "molecular"], 
       RowBox[{
        StyleBox["\[Psi]",
         FontWeight->"Bold"], "(", 
        RowBox[{
         StyleBox["r",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], ",", 
         StyleBox["R",
          FontWeight->"Bold"]}], ")"}]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"4019b8e2-2abc-574b-a617-0cf99df81563"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980346489083149*^9, 
  3.9803464914328976`*^9}},
 CellID->479770499,ExpressionUUID->"dcb3b0fe-3ed3-3a4e-8b10-ea651be2bddd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where the wavefunction depends on all electron coordinates ",
 StyleBox["r",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " and nuclear coordinates ",
 StyleBox["R",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox[".",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Text",
 CellID->389145815,ExpressionUUID->"f2a182e3-2b71-9741-9150-3dfe3481fab9"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Born\[Dash]Oppenheimer Approximation", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980343360043873*^9, 3.9803433636737137`*^9}},
 CellID->881288667,ExpressionUUID->"32816ac2-21c5-c847-b9c5-091cf6b1283c"],

Cell["\<\
Nuclei are roughly 2000 times heavier than electrons. They move on a much \
slower timescale. This separation of scales allows a powerful simplification: \
solve the electronic problem with the nuclei held fixed.\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->383717314,ExpressionUUID->"d083ef65-a22b-314e-9535-d9007ebafad3"],

Cell["\<\
Freezing the nuclei yields the electronic Hamiltonian:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980343385946045*^9, 3.980343417962517*^9}},
 CellID->267789140,ExpressionUUID->"f9db32a8-07a0-4a44-869a-95fe8de8fb95"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox["H", "^"], "elec"], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", 
         FractionBox["1", "2"]}], 
        RowBox[{
         UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
          RowBox[{" ", "i"}]], 
         RowBox[{
          SuperscriptBox[
           SubscriptBox["\[Del]", "i"], "2"], 
          RowBox[{"-", 
           SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
            RowBox[{" ", 
             RowBox[{"i", ",", "A"}]}]]}]}]}], 
        FractionBox[
         SubscriptBox["Z", "A"], 
         RowBox[{"|", 
          RowBox[{
           SubscriptBox[
            StyleBox["r",
             FontWeight->"Bold"], "i"], "-", 
           SubscriptBox[
            StyleBox["R",
             FontWeight->"Bold"], "A"]}], "|"}]]}], "+", 
       RowBox[{
        FractionBox["1", "2"], 
        RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
          RowBox[{" ", 
           RowBox[{"i", "!=", "j"}]}]], 
         FractionBox["1", 
          RowBox[{"|", 
           RowBox[{
            SubscriptBox[
             StyleBox["r",
              FontWeight->"Bold"], "i"], "-", 
            SubscriptBox[
             StyleBox["r",
              FontWeight->"Bold"], "j"]}], "|"}]]}]}], "+", 
       SubscriptBox["V", "NN"]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"c03fb6d3-2fbf-2244-8a5e-b8974c426392"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}},
 CellID->148788913,ExpressionUUID->"db14f6c5-35a0-d349-8a34-418427d2f49e"],

Cell["\<\
The four terms, in order, are: electron kinetic energy, electron-nucleus \
attraction, electron-electron repulsion, and the constant nuclear repulsion \
energy. The nuclear positions enter as parameters, not dynamical variables.\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->5158355,ExpressionUUID->"a2be76e4-35b6-fa4f-bebb-12c8109e3d56"],

Cell["\<\
After the Born-Oppenheimer approximation, we only need to describe electrons \
moving in the field of fixed nuclei. For each nuclear geometry, we solve:\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->712671864,ExpressionUUID->"a258768b-6413-9a40-b362-4c5fc641115e"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["H", "^"], "elec"], "(", 
        RowBox[{"\[InvisibleComma]", 
         StyleBox["R",
          FontWeight->"Bold"], "\[InvisibleComma]"}], ")"}], 
       StyleBox["\[Psi]",
        FontWeight->"Bold"]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["E", "elec"], 
       StyleBox["\[Psi]",
        FontWeight->"Bold"]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"600761d0-7b11-7a45-855a-bc1914bbf9ac"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}, {3.980357669890028*^9, 3.9803577631320953`*^9}, {
  3.980950593645277*^9, 3.9809506197097797`*^9}, {3.9809506935156345`*^9, 
  3.9809507479860973`*^9}},
 CellID->123091252,ExpressionUUID->"22bcba30-3f18-4f49-99a0-611239fd0836"],

Cell["\<\
But the electronic wavefunction still depends on the positions of all \
electrons:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9803464833901863`*^9},
 CellID->124436921,ExpressionUUID->"0540a041-a090-8343-a791-8b00de8d8b8b"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      StyleBox["\[Psi]",
       FontWeight->"Bold"], "(", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold"], "1"], ",", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold"], "2"], ",", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold"], "3"], ",", "\[Ellipsis]", ",", 
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["r",
         FontWeight->"Bold"], "N"]}], ")"}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"9e76e456-fdcd-894e-bf7c-f99ebef0ebcb"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980346489083149*^9, 
  3.9803464914328976`*^9}, {3.980346880978039*^9, 3.980346924569353*^9}},
 CellID->106937228,ExpressionUUID->"2b95a02c-0197-4f49-8448-aaa6437784a0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This function lives in a space of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"3", "N"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "98631129-908f-4c75-b4d0-debb003d2bab"],
 " dimensions. Even for 20 electrons, this function has 60 variables. Storing \
it on a classical grid requires memory that grows exponentially with the \
number of electrons. This exponential wall is not a failure of algorithms but \
it is a fundamental complexity barrier."
}], "Text",
 CellID->158334550,ExpressionUUID->"09f9ca8b-4d25-e34f-865a-faf4e298ea10"],

Cell["\<\
We need a radically different representation. This is where the key \
conceptual step begins.\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->751692875,ExpressionUUID->"f4a273e2-f21d-7844-9584-d5ab583dfa6a"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["From Continuous Physics to Discrete Orbitals", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.980345267845642*^9},
 CellID->135936158,ExpressionUUID->"ab715156-5efb-0347-8312-9fe9adc5a23c"],

Cell["\<\
The key move: instead of representing the many-electron wavefunction \
directly, first solve a single-particle problem:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9803479942835445`*^9, {3.9803490302643394`*^9, 3.980349044287937*^9}},
 CellID->181218768,ExpressionUUID->"9829c599-8547-b844-a445-20be7386d8a0"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["How does a single electron behave in the molecule?",
 FontFamily->"Georgia",
 FontWeight->"Normal",
 FontSlant->"Italic"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9803479942835445`*^9, 3.9803490302643394`*^9},
 TextAlignment->Center,
 CellID->123215708,ExpressionUUID->"1890f1d6-5412-b541-9789-636fccd09cdb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This leads to the concept of molecular orbitals. An orbital is a \
single-particle wavefunction ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "p"], "(", 
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold"], ")"}], "."}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "19da1bf9-ad31-2b46-a879-64e0ca9115de"],
 " Orbitals form a basis for electronic motion, analogous to Fourier modes \
forming a basis for periodic functions."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.980349435512348*^9, {3.980349466826004*^9, 3.980349498809845*^9}, 
   3.9809461407226505`*^9},
 CellID->205602240,ExpressionUUID->"96c2a21f-92fd-0543-bc29-850a5b85088a"],

Cell["\<\
The crucial approximation: we truncate to a finite set of orbitals. This \
converts an infinite continuous problem into a finite discrete one.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.980349435512348*^9, {3.980349466826004*^9, 3.980349531004322*^9}},
 CellID->543237567,ExpressionUUID->"f93cb88b-a56a-2a4e-a4e6-c4f426d8009b"],

Cell["\<\
Electrons live in a continuous space; our computational world does not. We \
discretize the problem using an orbital basis, so any state is a linear \
combination of basis elements:\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->22799753,ExpressionUUID->"f0caf355-2234-694e-a17c-98791bf430c2"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      TemplateBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
         RowBox[{"s", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]]},
       "Ket"], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "j"], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["c", "j"], 
        TemplateBox[{
          SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "j"]},
         "Ket"]}]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"960c3d0e-1a3a-344e-95d1-3336118d3c25"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980346489083149*^9, 
  3.9803464914328976`*^9}, {3.980346880978039*^9, 3.980346924569353*^9}, {
  3.980950309740383*^9, 3.9809503581043434`*^9}, {3.9809503901271057`*^9, 
  3.98095039031806*^9}},
 CellID->257145600,ExpressionUUID->"f12a8803-0ed7-264e-9ece-4b9de5e846b2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Instead of asking \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]",
 StyleBox["Where is each electron?\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " we ask:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803452897731667`*^9, 3.9803453311065407`*^9}, {
  3.9803557852992325`*^9, 3.9803557858197823`*^9}},
 CellID->243258230,ExpressionUUID->"3636e1f0-32ab-764e-b06f-5f3ea992f545"],

Cell[TextData[{
 " ",
 StyleBox["\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Which orbitals are occupied?\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803452897731667`*^9, 3.9803453311065407`*^9}, {
  3.9803557852992325`*^9, 3.980355793474869*^9}},
 TextAlignment->Center,
 CellID->720699526,ExpressionUUID->"2f540d3a-c69c-4b42-bccc-2768aae540a0"],

Cell["\<\
We move from particle positions to occupation numbers, a description that \
maps naturally onto qubits.\
\>", "Text",
 CellID->435743009,ExpressionUUID->"c575d373-d371-e643-ac82-7621e1c768e5"],

Cell["\<\
Electrons are fermions and they obey the Pauli exclusion principle:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803570326904144`*^9, 3.9803570548668194`*^9}, 
   3.9803570866978207`*^9},
 CellID->16252389,ExpressionUUID->"ce22e273-cb66-c849-bd27-431ec0d729ef"],

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]An orbital can contain at most \
one electron with a given spin\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]",
 FontSlant->"Italic"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803570607690353`*^9, 3.9803570650258656`*^9}},
 TextAlignment->Center,
 CellID->24117417,ExpressionUUID->"3fe302c5-7439-0349-a06c-187052d8d6a5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Each orbital can be empty (0) or occupied (1). This leads to the \
occupation-number representation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["n", "1"], 
       SubscriptBox["n", "2"], 
       SubscriptBox["n", "3"], 
       SubscriptBox["\[Ellipsis]n", "M"]}]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "87d8c15f-e047-864e-aa37-706aee3915a7"],
 " e.g. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"010101"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "21160149-0314-5442-80b6-d4a687b66ba6"],
 ". This is the Fock space representation. A string of binary occupation \
numbers. If this looks like a register of qubits, it should. This structural \
parallel is the physical reason quantum computers are natural for quantum \
chemistry."
}], "Text",
 CellID->15685971,ExpressionUUID->"70858ad6-dc0f-2245-9486-01f372bfb864"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Second Quantization: The Algebra of Occupation", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980355910078869*^9, 3.9803559180513687`*^9}},
 CellID->91368529,ExpressionUUID->"c048f18e-b90f-8c4d-82b9-26a68fbb1c7a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Tracking individual electrons is redundant\[LongDash]electrons are identical \
particles. Second quantization describes a",
 StyleBox["dding an electron to an orbital ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "or ",
 StyleBox["removing an electron from an orbital.",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980356860491123*^9, 3.980356893123991*^9}},
 CellID->296634899,ExpressionUUID->"afd70cd4-3512-d64a-890f-0cf72438aef7"],

Cell["The fundamental objects are:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980356860491123*^9, 3.9803569237844715`*^9}},
 CellID->53344533,ExpressionUUID->"5309f368-3cf8-d841-a29d-5129dcfdebbd"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Creation (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    SubscriptBox["a", "p"], "\[Dagger]"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6bd767ce-eafb-5d4a-8165-20d2503ff5dd"],
 "): places an electron in orbital p"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980356924799488*^9, 3.9803569535102234`*^9}},
 CellID->156390645,ExpressionUUID->"d4af216d-bd40-7f40-b2bb-1ffe45b159e5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Annihilation (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["a", "p"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "c0a8b4f3-3623-5745-bea8-e8dd9b0cdff2"],
 "): removes an electron from orbital p"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980356924799488*^9, 3.9803569958791676`*^9}},
 CellID->218432425,ExpressionUUID->"8eb5a4e2-623c-d048-a76f-cb386bd77b62"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
These obey the canonical anticommutation relations:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980945598529274*^9, 
  3.980945603450756*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"43389428-8b72-8649-a441-\
ae2c34d85f07"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          SubscriptBox["a", "p"], "\[Dagger]"], ",", 
         SubscriptBox["a", "q"]}], "}"}], "=", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Delta]", 
        RowBox[{"p", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]]}], " ", ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox["a", "p"], ",", 
         SubscriptBox["a", "q"]}], "}"}], "=", "0"}], " ", ",", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox[
          SubscriptBox["a", "p"], "\[Dagger]"], ",", 
         SuperscriptBox[
          SubscriptBox["a", "q"], "\[Dagger]"]}], "}"}], "=", " ", "0"}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"ae5e0877-a937-8e40-ba76-09dfecffcb6b"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}, {3.980357669890028*^9, 3.9803577631320953`*^9}, {
  3.9809456214382896`*^9, 3.980945693266716*^9}},
 CellID->144776397,ExpressionUUID->"8acbeb1b-e23c-c64f-85c9-52f9e3abf262"],

Cell["\<\
The anticommutation (rather than commutation) automatically enforces the \
Pauli principle: attempting to create two electrons in the same orbital \
gives zero.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809457753583164`*^9, 
  3.9809457855125065`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d39d7d8c-5462-1341-8f69-\
bfa410941035"],

Cell["In this language, the electronic Hamiltonian becomes:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.980357008757681*^9, {3.9803574188336716`*^9, 3.980357419079956*^9}, 
   3.9809457777523556`*^9},
 CellID->436213999,ExpressionUUID->"98c40256-2df6-8247-98a4-2439fc9d678d"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox[
       OverscriptBox["H", "^"], 
       RowBox[{"s", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        FractionBox["1", "2"], 
        RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
          RowBox[{"p", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]], 
         RowBox[{
          SubscriptBox["h", 
           RowBox[{"p", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]], 
          SuperscriptBox[
           SubscriptBox["a", "p"], "\[Dagger]"], 
          SubscriptBox["a", "q"]}]}]}], "+", 
       RowBox[{
        FractionBox["1", "2"], 
        RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
          RowBox[{
          "p", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q", "\[InvisibleComma]", "r", "\[InvisibleComma]",
            "s"}]], 
         RowBox[{
          SubscriptBox["h", 
           RowBox[{
           "p", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q", "\[InvisibleComma]", "r", "\[InvisibleComma]",
             "s"}]], 
          SuperscriptBox[
           SubscriptBox["a", "p"], "\[Dagger]"], 
          SuperscriptBox[
           SubscriptBox["a", "q"], "\[Dagger]"], 
          SubscriptBox["a", "r"], 
          SubscriptBox["a", "s"]}]}]}]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"ad54c5ad-0ee4-b64b-94d8-fd700427ec21"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}, {3.980357669890028*^9, 3.9803577631320953`*^9}, {
  3.98095058034367*^9, 3.9809505870097065`*^9}},
 CellID->238798026,ExpressionUUID->"7e7ce70c-b7b3-3e42-9955-594d7b929bfc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The structure separates into one-body and two-body contributions, encoded \
in the coefficients ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", 
    RowBox[{"p", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "221aba27-5e95-4248-adbb-1aa2458a8654"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "pqrs"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "bfc11a15-1119-d246-b0ae-d5481900c0d5"],
 ", respectively. The one-body integrals encode kinetic energy and the \
nuclear potential; the two-body integrals encode Coulomb repulsion. These \
are computed classically from the orbital basis. What remains is to find \
the ground state\[LongDash]the hard part."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980357778107029*^9, 3.9803577990148773`*^9}, 
   3.9805109430745754`*^9, {3.980945724706871*^9, 3.980945750711916*^9}, {
   3.980950003835518*^9, 3.9809500320902996`*^9}},
 CellID->244144000,ExpressionUUID->"fe34add6-94d9-9f4e-8531-f575cc1327e5"],

Cell["Physically:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f877a68a-3096-1b4b-9406-b9dc518b339d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", 
    RowBox[{"p", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "14ae4799-56a0-fa4f-b685-2378bdb2e92a"],
 " gives the amplitude for an electron hopping from orbital ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["q", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "315f7e14-1756-234a-9177-0ffc28ac67e8"],
 " to orbital ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"p", "."}], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "8a4c3d6b-f7d2-fd4c-b77a-30a438322c3b"],
 " "
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809500379742775`*^9, 
  3.9809500469964447`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6bcb497a-f529-4748-9fcf-\
b1967c062c6b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["h", "pqrs"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "b060fa4f-5495-ce47-a430-cc64b14bde39"],
 " encodes the scattering of two electrons from orbitals ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["r", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "16274243-6371-664f-96a9-fea54e9d31fb"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["s", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "02554185-ec72-8242-852c-8af03687fdcf"],
 " into orbitals ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["p", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "16e812f3-f469-8e4b-85f8-84ac7545b70b"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["q", TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "fe84183e-55f7-db45-89eb-f5b403a609b0"],
 "."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809500379742775`*^9, 
  3.9809500836400547`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"24d24337-00ce-bd4e-a9a8-\
e9933b20b1d8"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
The eigenvalue problem in second-quantized form:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980950572679468*^9, 
  3.980950573907345*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c4a46d3a-f8bf-2647-8d1b-\
8f4432a810d3"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["H", "^"], 
        RowBox[{"s", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]], 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
          RowBox[{"s", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]]},
        "Ket"]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["E", "elec"], 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", 
          RowBox[{"s", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]]},
        "Ket"]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"d56e1c37-e497-1548-a8c6-38b534c1b0a1"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}, {3.980357669890028*^9, 3.9803577631320953`*^9}, {
  3.980950593645277*^9, 3.9809506197097797`*^9}, {3.9809506935156345`*^9, 
  3.9809506935156345`*^9}},
 CellID->100661301,ExpressionUUID->"7981357b-11b1-e043-867a-3acae8ff65db"],

Cell["\<\
The problem has been reduced from continuous electronic coordinates to a \
discrete fermionic operator problem. The Hamiltonian is ready to be mapped \
to qubits.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809507910578365`*^9, 
  3.980950795978794*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"872e982a-d603-e248-8fd4-\
ba9eb15d9bdd"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["From Fermions to Qubits", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.980357972995737*^9},
 CellID->45591065,ExpressionUUID->"9e4b84b0-29ed-5b41-81d4-80611145f178"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Although ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    OverscriptBox["H", "^"], 
    RowBox[{"s", "\[InvisibleComma]", "q"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"ce697ade-32de-7b4a-8691-2eeb72cab48f"],
 " is discrete, it is still written in terms of fermionic operators. \
Creation and annihilation operators anticommute; Pauli operators on \
different qubits commute. A faithful mapping must encode the fermionic \
sign structure into the qubit representation. Quantum hardware manipulates \
qubits via Pauli operators:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809512986882915`*^9, 
  3.980951306738987*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9f880282-c729-ba45-b6ee-\
f98bc665ac36"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"MatrixForm", "@", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", "#", "]"}], "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", 
     "]"}]}], "&"}], "/@", 
  RowBox[{"{", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<X\>\"", ",", "\"\<Y\>\"", ",", "\"\<Z\>\"", 
    ",", "\"\<I\>\""}], "}"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980951310619869*^9, 3.9809513131910057`*^9}, {
  3.9809513675596714`*^9, 3.980951415362917*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[3]:=",ExpressionUUID->"36fff5b3-e923-3646-90f6-e7ec2c5ee240"],

Cell["\<\
A mapping from fermionic operators to qubit operators is therefore required.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809517575797462`*^9, 
  3.980951787705391*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cf2f0921-5933-5744-8d4b-\
20e46a4cce9b"],

Cell["The standard mappings:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803579874493847`*^9, 3.9803580000223904`*^9}, {
   3.9809517738126984`*^9, 3.980951793093382*^9}, 3.9809552291193867`*^9},
 CellID->261545918,ExpressionUUID->"6a0dc7c9-45db-a042-8b72-25ce98d3e79d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Jordan\[Dash]Wigner", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803580013406906`*^9, 3.9803580033211193`*^9}},
 CellID->13695961,ExpressionUUID->"e39479df-0e16-1442-aba2-6cfdcb4c0c44"],

Cell["Bravyi\[Dash]Kitaev", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803580070854073`*^9, 3.9803580073094254`*^9}},
 CellID->31433872,ExpressionUUID->"291b96d5-7dd3-bd4f-9adb-743807ec8666"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
Each systematically rewrites creation and annihilation operators as tensor \
products of Pauli matrices.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980951138918003*^9, 
  3.9809511411203384`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"788a6745-a7a1-6b45-8c07-\
279319b4fea4"],

Cell["\<\
Under the Jordan\[Dash]Wigner transformation, the creation operator becomes:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980951138918003*^9, 3.980951143854866*^9}, {
  3.9809552323080425`*^9, 
  3.980955234680315*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"7ade5f6c-551f-e34a-8635-\
0451cead0b79"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox[
       SubscriptBox["a", "p"], "\[Dagger]"], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["1", "2"], 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{
          SubscriptBox["X", "p"], "-", "\[ImaginaryI]"}], "\[InvisibleComma]", 
         SubscriptBox["Y", "p"]}], ")"}], 
       RowBox[{
        UnderscriptBox["\[Product]", 
         RowBox[{"j", "<", "p"}]], 
        SubscriptBox["Z", "j"]}]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"cd8949f7-af58-6046-aaf2-128f7f69276e"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}, {3.980357669890028*^9, 3.9803577631320953`*^9}, {
  3.9809456214382896`*^9, 3.980945693266716*^9}, {3.980951155027975*^9, 
  3.9809511815899353`*^9}, {3.9809512239896927`*^9, 3.9809512667410088`*^9}},
 CellID->109862864,ExpressionUUID->"a0424106-1f5e-8742-a942-176a9484ef0a"],

Cell["\<\
After applying either mapping, the Hamiltonian takes the form:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803579874493847`*^9, 3.9803580103419704`*^9}, {
  3.9809552784939938`*^9, 3.9809552797513847`*^9}},
 CellID->168386437,ExpressionUUID->"7bc608b9-a24d-934f-8264-e6af0f95d9e4"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      OverscriptBox["H", "^"], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["\[Sum]", "j"], 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["c", "j"], 
        SubscriptBox["P", "j"]}]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"046dcaaa-cd61-bc4c-bc5d-0475984e0c80"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}, {3.980357669890028*^9, 3.9803577631320953`*^9}, {
  3.9803580195445385`*^9, 3.9803580334405193`*^9}},
 CellID->564503411,ExpressionUUID->"0f6700d7-97e4-f145-a337-dc7cd771086a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where each ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["P", "j"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9582b347-61f9-494c-94e5-ca7e98c9c907"],
 " is a Pauli string, e.g. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["X", "0"], 
    SubscriptBox["Z", "1"], 
    SubscriptBox["Z", "2"], 
    SubscriptBox["Y", "3"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1a9dff65-0f02-fd41-a7e2-2da011dbbecf"],
 ". The real coefficients are determined by the molecular integrals and the \
chosen mapping. This is the Hamiltonian VQE works with: a weighted sum of \
Pauli strings, each directly measurable on quantum hardware."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.980358040909174*^9, 3.980358095646847*^9}},
 CellID->534696157,ExpressionUUID->"6f089b2f-4408-d943-8bdc-091783e17f64"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The fermionic occupation basis ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["n", 
        RowBox[{"m", "-", "1"}]], 
       SubscriptBox["\[Ellipsis]n", "0"]}]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "ce00ebf1-306c-b34a-8295-acd9452c8af3"],
 " maps naturally onto a qubit register ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["q", 
        RowBox[{"m", "-", "1"}]], 
       SubscriptBox["\[Ellipsis]q", "0"]}]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],
  FormatType->TraditionalForm,ExpressionUUID->
  "4618498b-4d8c-2a45-956f-45213f58f645"],
 "\[LongDash]each orbital becomes one qubit, with q \[Element] {0,1}."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809553366706314`*^9, 
  3.980955373664751*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e62545d2-4040-f246-befb-\
e32eb66462cb"],

Cell["\<\
The eigenvalue problem in qubit form:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9809553817397537`*^9, 
  3.9809553879761353`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a1da66b4-33af-7946-95aa-\
5c26cd68c843"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["H", "^"], "qubit"], 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "qubit"]},
        "Ket"]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["E", "elec"], 
       TemplateBox[{
         SubscriptBox["\[Psi]", "qubit"]},
        "Ket"]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"3f81566d-5c8a-c144-91c6-0071766bb548"]], \
"Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9803393323717976`*^9, 3.9803393557359314`*^9}, {
  3.9803428483546295`*^9, 3.9803428886617928`*^9}, {3.980343427303955*^9, 
  3.980343663243046*^9}, {3.980357669890028*^9, 3.9803577631320953`*^9}, {
  3.980950593645277*^9, 3.9809506197097797`*^9}, {3.9809506935156345`*^9, 
  3.9809506935156345`*^9}, {3.9809553915316925`*^9, 3.9809554064449863`*^9}},
 CellID->167191840,ExpressionUUID->"c8bec862-f993-1947-ac24-fd60c76727cb"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The Variational Quantum Eigensolver", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.652728456208679*^9, 3.652728527108994*^9, {3.973950904885639*^9, 
   3.9739509056377277`*^9}, {3.98095542591267*^9, 3.980955453581709*^9}},
 CellID->1564634076,ExpressionUUID->"41bb3d67-bcc1-4878-b10f-288e763fd3b8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The variational principle is the mathematical engine of VQE. For any \
normalized trial state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"], "."}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d4137b1c-7d62-490d-8971-25d4800e8c49"],
 " the expectation value of the Hamiltonian is an upper bound to the true \
ground-state energy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["E", "o"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f13f4ef4-df42-414b-a40d-f5e1829a3007"],
 " associated with a Hamiltonian ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["H", "^"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "59974a1a-2358-477e-86d4-003d0e02b1f2"],
 ":"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548543060668125`*^9, 3.954854376644642*^9}},
 CellID->1643310945,ExpressionUUID->"ed00b29e-63aa-4184-ae28-1cb11faae862"],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox["E", "0"], "<=", 
       FractionBox[
        RowBox[{
         TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
          "Bra"], 
         OverscriptBox["H", "^"], 
         TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
          "Ket"]}], 
        TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]", "\[Psi]"},
         "BraKet"]]}], "=", 
      RowBox[{"\[LeftAngleBracket]", " ", "H", " ", "\[RightAngleBracket]"}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"a48f8cdd-dca7-4e1c-b098-cfc8c3473c5c"]], \
"Text",
 CellID->339868548,ExpressionUUID->"ad848ed7-ff9e-4e85-899e-a02b6e5af62f"],

Cell["The physical content: you can never underestimate the ground-state energy \
by guessing. Every trial state gives an energy that is too high (or exactly \
right). Minimization is therefore a well-posed problem. In this equation:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954854384099882*^9, 3.9548543893053875`*^9}},
 CellID->2011668863,ExpressionUUID->"68f7fdfe-d188-4617-84e1-70f558656bb9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["E", "0"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c243bbaf-d07a-4ace-8f66-20616f48b250"],
 "\:200b is the true ground state energy"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954854390070236*^9, 3.954854400438629*^9}},
 CellID->136042073,ExpressionUUID->"896fa5d9-1502-4e32-9768-f8b40cc0baf2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["H", "^"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e1d3f1f3-6721-4ca4-8eb0-89d28a75dec6"],
 " is the Hamiltonian operator"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954854390070236*^9, 3.9548544111521416`*^9}},
 CellID->1536520503,ExpressionUUID->"ea874ca7-ae59-4d1c-9425-fc609cbb0d26"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0df59f5d-4e57-4596-a36a-5d2c7b64df89"],
 " is the trial wavefunction"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954854390070236*^9, 3.954854440092451*^9}, {
  3.9548551726533833`*^9, 3.9548551855275803`*^9}},
 CellID->809238746,ExpressionUUID->"a9e8c586-e282-4df4-acef-9b27b7692156"],

Cell[TextData[{
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]", "\[Psi]"},
    "BraKet"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5ff2c686-01cc-48c8-b152-fa481c7608f1"],
 " ensures normalization"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954854390070236*^9, 3.954854440092451*^9}, {
  3.9548551726533833`*^9, 3.9548552144768505`*^9}, {3.9803389268420773`*^9, 
  3.9803389268430786`*^9}},
 CellID->861667571,ExpressionUUID->"c2371f57-93a5-4d6f-9fcb-46790db68613"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Objective", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548553385194244`*^9, 3.9548553395475616`*^9}},
 CellID->623600062,ExpressionUUID->"d921e306-8692-4166-b285-9a323f0da44a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The VQE objective: find a parametrized trial state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "34428d53-edac-4ce7-9bcc-2ec9528fa4fe"],
 " so that the energy expectation value is minimized."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548552249706917`*^9, 3.954855243188137*^9}},
 CellID->1126044674,ExpressionUUID->"6ebc887c-9954-4049-9c10-361e88ee0d0a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Find optimal parameters ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
     "Ket"], "\[Congruent]", 
    TemplateBox[{
      RowBox[{"\[Psi]", "(", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Theta]", "opt"], ")"}]},
     "Ket"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ed17b9dd-acce-40f8-a36b-0dc8bc22736c"],
 " such that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[LeftAngleBracket]", " ", 
     OverscriptBox["H", "^"], "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], "->", 
    SubscriptBox["E", "0"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0523befb-24c7-480f-9ae4-9cbd22f6606f"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954855253567894*^9, 3.954855256451542*^9}},
 CellID->1806938554,ExpressionUUID->"6d7b6e37-4eac-407d-ab78-b689d49b35d9"],

Cell["\<\
From an information-theoretic standpoint, the variational principle converts \
the eigenvalue problem (find the lowest eigenvalue of an exponentially large \
matrix) into an optimization problem (minimize a real-valued function over \
a parameter space).\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954855248985567*^9},
 CellID->1650024851,ExpressionUUID->"0941012d-8d61-4588-bd04-870f5e7a60d2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Mathematically: approximate the eigenvector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bf5fac40-bbb8-465d-a67f-7640ebc82155"],
 " of H corresponding to its lowest eigenvalue, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["E", "0"], " ", "."}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2bad138d-3ef9-45c7-b814-4fb96afa2582"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548552690301895`*^9, 3.9548552842777386`*^9}},
 CellID->1511337046,ExpressionUUID->"d7600820-afe2-40be-917e-5684e27d50ab"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Implementation", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954855352139847*^9, 3.954855355672674*^9}},
 CellID->605155406,ExpressionUUID->"35e702d2-6496-4a80-8206-7e66b2631d1b"],

Cell["\<\
To solve this on a quantum computer, define a parametrized ansatz\[LongDash]a \
trial wavefunction implemented as a sequence of quantum gates. Quantum \
computers can only perform unitary operations and measurements, so the \
ansatz must be a unitary circuit.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954855313924715*^9, 3.9548553848033695`*^9},
 CellID->364356450,ExpressionUUID->"ef514af6-626a-4629-8315-b8bf979b4cad"],

Cell["Ansatz construction", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954855394284876*^9, 3.9548554043863735`*^9}},
 CellID->1262977553,ExpressionUUID->"37a3822e-c35c-4a1b-8156-82ef8dad8bfe"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "The wavefunction ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"\[Psi]"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d7a7aa22-cc30-48d7-a94f-04697b02259f"],
 " is prepared by applying a parametrized unitary ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"U", 
    RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d8849aae-2a1a-418f-a49b-ffc7094ed227"],
 " to the initial state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{"0"},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1f593f38-fcd9-400a-bd4c-447364c87354"],
 " (all qubits in the ground state)."
}], "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954855394284876*^9, 3.9548554229962044`*^9}},
 CellID->1135366323,ExpressionUUID->"5576fae2-cd57-43f4-a4a2-a703bc236be3"],

Cell["\<\
The VQE cost function is the energy expectation value:\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954855439448923*^9, 3.954855439677862*^9}, {
  3.954855470548071*^9, 3.9548554717298527`*^9}},
 CellID->1709587066,ExpressionUUID->"f9400372-d214-4657-a5fb-58f2c5cc95d0"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[GridBox[{
    {
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["E", "VQE"], "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        StyleBox["min",
         FontSlant->"Italic"], "\[Theta]"], 
       TemplateBox[{"0"},
        "Bra"], 
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox["U", "\[Dagger]"], "(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
       OverscriptBox["H", "^"], 
       RowBox[{"U", "(", "\[Theta]", ")"}], 
       TemplateBox[{"0"},
        "Ket"]}]}]}
   },
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{
        Scaled[0.96]}}}], 
  TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->"56d1e6b1-7b75-4207-bc18-43c993ae5742"]], \
"Text",
 CellID->1846105049,ExpressionUUID->"8ce79bbe-cd87-49e3-8f4e-168aaeba8567"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "where U(\[Theta]) is the ansatz circuit with parameters ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]", "\[Element]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", "\[Pi]"}], ",", "\[Pi]"}]}]}], "]"}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"5b92d740-3a1b-4548-af73-4d13dd81260f"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellID->643826687,ExpressionUUID->"b21b19ee-f165-44dd-a806-592bcba5dff6"],

Cell["\<\
The objective: minimize this cost function with respect to the parameters \
\[Theta]. The quantum computer measures each Pauli string in the Hamiltonian \
decomposition; the classical computer assembles the expectation value and \
updates the parameters.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.9548554827014885`*^9, {3.9548560832054253`*^9, 3.9548560853140507`*^9}},
 CellID->1772514823,ExpressionUUID->"d5630ed1-fedd-466d-9d48-95972206344f"],

Cell["\<\
At the optimum, the cost function approximates the ground-state energy. The \
choice of ansatz determines what states are reachable\[LongDash]if the ground state \
lies outside the ansatz family, VQE finds the best approximation within it.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9548560892480907`*^9},
 CellID->763478977,ExpressionUUID->"77f22c02-d169-4d4f-be5b-0d08e97b1e76"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Initial Example", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.966342675377556*^9, 3.9663426769055233`*^9}, {
  3.973950508308221*^9, 3.973950510567564*^9}},
 CellID->196891901,ExpressionUUID->"59b25f95-4899-dd42-8821-8a0a68cfe4ee"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To see VQE in action, consider driving a variational state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.915203395207388*^9, 3.915203505025005*^9}, 
    3.915203571750614*^9, {3.915203669068693*^9, 3.915203677164776*^9}, {
    3.915709635507417*^9, 3.915709735629401*^9}, {3.915709787828616*^9, 
    3.915709840893857*^9}, {3.915709972850725*^9, 3.915710018714433*^9}, {
    3.915710182677065*^9, 3.915710183938304*^9}, {3.915721337712696*^9, 
    3.9157213652040544`*^9}, 3.916931232284334*^9, {3.9180495814172378`*^9, 
    3.918049643709629*^9}, {3.918049828979373*^9, 3.918049869552479*^9}, {
    3.918819304806325*^9, 3.9188193066521435`*^9}, 3.919522990616638*^9, {
    3.927220272431951*^9, 3.927220277061597*^9}, {3.933932853769938*^9, 
    3.9339329303522077`*^9}, {3.933932974920411*^9, 3.933932977795932*^9}},
  TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->
  "182d71ec-b530-9e4c-8a91-ad8b8035b52a"],
 " to the ground state of a single-qubit Hamiltonian:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9397374132018523`*^9, 3.9397374962676697`*^9}, {
  3.939740880755435*^9, 3.939740881430128*^9}, {3.96634270736191*^9, 
  3.9663427124592*^9}},
 CellID->383766527,ExpressionUUID->"78c0db46-1800-bc4b-9e99-5a2263eeb945"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"H", "=", 
  RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<X\>\"", "+", "\"\<Z\>\""}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939312557244169*^9, 3.9393125669058447`*^9}, {
  3.939312604250048*^9, 3.939312605140509*^9}, {3.9393130712863216`*^9, 
  3.939313101079802*^9}, {3.939313442943426*^9, 3.9393134440414104`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[3]:=",
 CellID->37529228,ExpressionUUID->"186dc7f9-e147-1b4d-bf1d-d0298b93d7ac"],

Cell["The ansatz: an RX rotation followed by an RY rotation. Together, these can \
reach any point on the Bloch sphere, so the ansatz is complete for this \
problem. Define V(\[Theta]):", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939316077230785*^9, 3.939316088591893*^9}},
 CellID->108853686,ExpressionUUID->"239a0caf-3db3-3240-8d5c-a1a9ce8c02ee"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"V", "=", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<0\>\"", ",", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"\"\<RX\>\"", "[", "\[Theta]1", "]"}], "->", 
        RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}]}], ",", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"\"\<RY\>\"", "[", "\[Theta]2", "]"}], "->", 
        RowBox[{"{", "1", "}"}]}]}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<Parameters\>\"", "->", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", "\[Theta]2"}], "}"}]}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"\"\<Diagram\>\"", "//", "V"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939312650878281*^9, 3.9393126655333424`*^9}, {
   3.939312703159622*^9, 3.939312795393164*^9}, {3.939313422485044*^9, 
   3.9393134248332577`*^9}, {3.939313962725342*^9, 3.939314010335967*^9}, 
   3.9393160903610077`*^9, 3.9397375666573777`*^9, {3.939822715826296*^9, 
   3.9398227229890966`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[27]:=",
 CellID->385654644,ExpressionUUID->"e5ff8e87-6ecf-4846-9050-54d2ba843857"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The trial state ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Phi]", " ", 
       RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}]},
    "Ket"], TraditionalForm]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.915203395207388*^9, 3.915203505025005*^9}, 
    3.915203571750614*^9, {3.915203669068693*^9, 3.915203677164776*^9}, {
    3.915709635507417*^9, 3.915709735629401*^9}, {3.915709787828616*^9, 
    3.915709840893857*^9}, {3.915709972850725*^9, 3.915710018714433*^9}, {
    3.915710182677065*^9, 3.915710183938304*^9}, {3.915721337712696*^9, 
    3.9157213652040544`*^9}, 3.916931232284334*^9, {3.9180495814172378`*^9, 
    3.918049643709629*^9}, {3.918049828979373*^9, 3.918049869552479*^9}, {
    3.918819304806325*^9, 3.9188193066521435`*^9}, 3.919522990616638*^9, {
    3.927220272431951*^9, 3.927220277061597*^9}, {3.933932853769938*^9, 
    3.9339329303522077`*^9}, {3.933932974920411*^9, 3.933932977795932*^9}},
  TextAlignment->Center,ExpressionUUID->
  "684feae2-5dee-d74d-8e8b-d7165e99a490"],
 " from the circuit V:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939316099967835*^9, 3.939316128312606*^9}, {
  3.939731137027725*^9, 3.939731146307087*^9}, {3.939737543561979*^9, 
  3.939737571415374*^9}},
 CellID->240142195,ExpressionUUID->"e0206dc5-61f7-9b4c-b581-6245b11d2164"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[Phi]", "=", 
   RowBox[{"V", "[", "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"\"\<Formula\>\"", "//", "\[Phi]"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.939314020057344*^9, 3.939316095713163*^9, {3.939316488098091*^9, 
   3.93931649500105*^9}, {3.939740895999033*^9, 3.939740902095635*^9}, {
   3.939824785908279*^9, 3.9398248162816706`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[69]:=",
 CellID->8141304,ExpressionUUID->"bdc28ff1-d7d9-4f44-8ce4-f59685a416cd"],

Cell["The cost function \[ScriptCapitalL]:", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9393161331633782`*^9, 3.9393161366676364`*^9}, {
  3.939737524263297*^9, 3.93973753461891*^9}, {3.939740823147156*^9, 
  3.939740833314873*^9}},
 CellID->101917928,ExpressionUUID->"711007fc-8c60-8b42-ae1b-b1e97f0264c2"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalL]", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1_", ",", "\[Theta]2_"}], "]"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{"ComplexExpand", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\"\<Scalar\>\"", "//", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["\[Phi]", "\[Dagger]"], "@", 
      RowBox[{"H", "@", "\[Phi]"}]}]}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalL]", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", " ", "\[Theta]2"}], "]"}], "//", 
  "Simplify"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939314037565735*^9, 3.9393140898220415`*^9}, {
   3.939731402252567*^9, 3.939731470489509*^9}, {3.9397316633820295`*^9, 
   3.939731676538597*^9}, {3.939731729161224*^9, 3.9397317487027683`*^9}, {
   3.93973758499294*^9, 3.9397375853901854`*^9}, 3.939740748085252*^9, {
   3.939740812705102*^9, 3.939740820361878*^9}, {3.939740905359081*^9, 
   3.939740906483289*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[8]:=",
 CellID->424411615,ExpressionUUID->"6b652a21-d36c-8742-ad45-f80de6eaedcd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Minimize to find the ground-state energy of ",
 StyleBox["H",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ":"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9393161500297165`*^9, 3.939316155194723*^9}, {
  3.939737593809981*^9, 3.9397376202822633`*^9}},
 CellID->180028484,ExpressionUUID->"d37c8a6c-4111-4349-9897-36e03938e092"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"MinValue", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalL]", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", " ", "\[Theta]2"}], "]"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", " ", "\[Theta]2"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939314264096307*^9, 3.939314265750436*^9}, 
   3.9393143123201866`*^9, 3.939314360873497*^9, {3.939314397959459*^9, 
   3.939314420241147*^9}, 3.939731681504419*^9, 3.939740839237777*^9},
 CellLabel->"In[10]:=",
 CellID->125589518,ExpressionUUID->"81e04afd-91b7-ed41-94bb-7b41ad9c36d5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Visualizations", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9397319450786967`*^9, 3.939731947995684*^9}},
 CellID->156347761,ExpressionUUID->"b7f337a8-62fa-6747-9af3-ad368f84283e"],

Cell["\<\
To observe the optimizer\[CloseCurlyQuote]s trajectory, we run gradient \
descent from an initial guess:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939734902103387*^9, 3.939734963216844*^9}},
 CellID->115876355,ExpressionUUID->"f872908e-5330-7240-b1e7-752b5df8ff9b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"initialPosition", "=", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"0.1", ",", "0.1"}], "}"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9398225787100677`*^9, 3.939822595266068*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[20]:=",
 CellID->384946293,ExpressionUUID->"bf3cbf25-bf74-9f49-a711-0ebec56b8eab"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"params", "=", 
   RowBox[{"GradientDescent", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalL]", ",", "initialPosition"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939734966405398*^9, 3.939734981318858*^9}, 
   3.939740848684093*^9, {3.939822557611044*^9, 3.939822559988126*^9}, {
   3.939822591631957*^9, 3.9398225983962574`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[21]:=",
 CellID->238472348,ExpressionUUID->"b74e0571-5031-d043-8e9b-985a2dcb9164"],

Cell["\<\
The cost function values at each step:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939734997162181*^9, 3.939735017063183*^9}},
 CellID->471602276,ExpressionUUID->"5a5252d7-5107-2947-b02d-33a19988773c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"costs", "=", 
   RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalL]", "@@@", "params"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939735021311099*^9, 3.939735027029743*^9}, 
   3.939740850238646*^9, 3.9398225075400705`*^9},
 CellLabel->"In[22]:=",
 CellID->29707283,ExpressionUUID->"84561fa0-cfde-1349-a9be-3dac6361a3c7"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Cost curve", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.93973212645317*^9, 3.93973212890716*^9}},
 CellID->68288565,ExpressionUUID->"8c1a7dd6-abd1-8b45-96b7-39c522a5b917"],

Cell["\<\
The loss curve shows the cost function decreasing monotonically toward the \
exact ground-state energy:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9397311607091217`*^9, 3.939731176519654*^9}, {
  3.93973195265976*^9, 3.939731954192539*^9}, {3.939731984882383*^9, 
  3.93973200204299*^9}, {3.939732131509432*^9, 3.93973215082154*^9}},
 CellID->494770625,ExpressionUUID->"6ec8a410-baa4-5a4a-a3be-ec02adeb978d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ListLinePlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{"costs", ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotRange", "\[Rule]", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"0", ",", "15"}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"-", "1.5`"}], ",", "0.1`"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"PlotLabel", "\[Rule]", "\"\<Loss Curve\>\""}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"Frame", "\[Rule]", "True"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"GridLines", "\[Rule]", "Automatic"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"FrameLabel", "\[Rule]", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<Step\>\"", ",", "\"\<Cost function\>\""}], "}"}]}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"ImageMargins", "\[Rule]", "1"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{"Epilog", "\[Rule]", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"Red", ",", "Dashed", ",", 
        RowBox[{"Line", "[", 
         RowBox[{"{", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"0", ",", 
             RowBox[{"-", 
              SqrtBox["2"]}]}], "}"}], ",", 
           RowBox[{"{", 
            RowBox[{"15", ",", 
             RowBox[{"-", 
              SqrtBox["2"]}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"Red", ",", 
        RowBox[{"Inset", "[", 
         RowBox[{"\"\<-\!\(\*SqrtBox[\(2\)]\)\>\"", ",", 
          RowBox[{"{", 
           RowBox[{"2", ",", 
            RowBox[{"-", "1.3`"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}]}], 
  "\[IndentingNewLine]", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9397318551064696`*^9, 3.939731891416993*^9}, {
   3.939732034868556*^9, 3.939732111342974*^9}, {3.939735020146452*^9, 
   3.9397350308864594`*^9}, {3.939736049585041*^9, 3.939736065831478*^9}, {
   3.939736414718851*^9, 3.939736477749852*^9}, {3.9397368105672684`*^9, 
   3.9397368224184732`*^9}, {3.939736857046258*^9, 3.9397369075877247`*^9}, {
   3.939736947343971*^9, 3.9397369770186734`*^9}, {3.9397371241021547`*^9, 
   3.9397371832918363`*^9}, {3.939737249841279*^9, 3.93973731308212*^9}, {
   3.9397377172198086`*^9, 3.9397378004948273`*^9}, 3.9663434606764755`*^9, {
   3.966343504148407*^9, 3.96634352905299*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[23]:=",
 CellID->23035234,ExpressionUUID->"9241bdf2-1e53-cb4a-b817-69260bd219d1"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Parameter Space", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939737695652274*^9, 3.9397377059084992`*^9}},
 CellID->165329638,ExpressionUUID->"24ad949c-bab5-df4b-8a93-e36e36038917"],

Cell["\<\
The contour plot of the cost function reveals the landscape the optimizer \
navigates\[LongDash]periodic valleys from the trigonometric structure of rotation \
gates:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.939732139940488*^9, 3.939732164239072*^9}, {
  3.9397327243849754`*^9, 3.93973272789721*^9}, {3.9397348954850473`*^9, 
  3.939734896230008*^9}},
 CellID->471247251,ExpressionUUID->"2b482e3b-8bb9-7e4a-8c72-5cc3f3d02ca0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ContourPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalL]", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", "\[Theta]2"}], "]"}], ",", 
   InterpretationBox[
    DynamicModuleBox[{Typeset`open = False}, 
     TemplateBox[{"Expression", "SequenceIcon", 
       GridBox[{{
