}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Quantum Chemistry", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954856786439764*^9, 3.954856788420601*^9}, {
  3.955204527295431*^9, 3.955204529262594*^9}},
 CellID->680823082,ExpressionUUID->"9d6be7f2-9e94-e246-bfee-1ef03af2f5c9"],

Cell["\<\
VQE finds the ground-state energy of a molecular Hamiltonian\[LongDash]an \
optimization problem where the energy is minimized over the circuit parameters.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954856802016641*^9, 3.9548568130448*^9}},
 CellID->378016220,ExpressionUUID->"e97f4bf6-0ce3-8245-a4d9-cacdd64d2279"],

Cell["\<\
The parametrized circuit approximates the ground state; the optimizer drives \
the energy expectation value toward the true minimum.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.95485681455707*^9},
 CellID->313593419,ExpressionUUID->"b4ffbb53-3e19-7144-a4fb-42330e758e62"],

Cell["\<\
Beyond the energy itself, repeating VQE at different nuclear geometries maps \
out the potential energy surface\[LongDash]the function whose minimum determines \
the equilibrium molecular geometry.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9548568079298763`*^9},
 CellID->133122036,ExpressionUUID->"6ed71b20-cc76-e746-b7e0-0a96a84250cd"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Toy ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["H", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0a9e448d-8b23-394c-b782-a5bc7b0061bf"],
 " Molecule"
}], "Subsubsection",
 CellID->343672531,ExpressionUUID->"d273a073-af21-7441-ae24-8d3f9421b8d0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Consider the hydrogen molecule. Under symmetry reductions, the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["H", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c8c7d42f-5abf-fb40-9a8f-b60c7ca23d48"],
 " Hamiltonian can be modeled with two qubits:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548561407182*^9, 3.9548561477938223`*^9}},
 CellID->534718527,ExpressionUUID->"b1030766-5965-1c4d-90ea-203bda9676ac"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"H2", "=", 
  RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<ZI\>\"", "+", "\"\<IZ\>\""}], ")"}]}], "+", 
    RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "*", "\"\<XX\>\""}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[89]:=",
 CellID->162249822,ExpressionUUID->"fe7966a7-10ed-d843-be2c-21d45224e049"],

Cell["The physical content: the ZI + IZ terms represent on-site energies of the \
two spin-orbitals, while the XX term encodes the exchange interaction. For \
nonzero \[Beta], the ground state is entangled\[LongDash]no product-state ansatz \
can reach it. We proceed with the VQE steps:", "Text",
 CellID->604239,ExpressionUUID->"e53f941e-f659-9e42-bcca-fdee621f6e71"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["First:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " ",
 StyleBox["Parametrized quantum circuits, state and ansatz preparation. ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954856174402658*^9, 3.95485617460935*^9}, {
  3.954856236137745*^9, 3.954856243762686*^9}},
 CellID->235330201,ExpressionUUID->"8f227384-fa96-7c44-a19c-2da364e16e9d"],

Cell["\<\
A hardware-efficient ansatz with two layers of RY rotations and a CNOT gate. \
The CNOT is essential: it introduces entanglement between the two qubits, \
allowing the ansatz to represent correlated states that product states cannot.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954856245173311*^9, 3.9548562508430824`*^9}},
 CellID->128943131,ExpressionUUID->"30911ceb-d907-5541-a7ba-e9c4e6a255e2"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"HEAnsatz", "=", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<00\>\"", ",", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<RY\>\"", "[", 
        RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Theta]1"}], "]"}], "->", "1"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<RY\>\"", "[", 
        RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Theta]2"}], "]"}], "->", "2"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", "->", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"1", ",", "2"}], "}"}]}], ",", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<RY\>\"", "[", 
        RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Theta]3"}], "]"}], "->", "1"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"\"\<RY\>\"", "[", 
        RowBox[{"2", " ", "\[Theta]4"}], "]"}], "->", "2"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}],
   ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{"HEAnsatz", "[", "\"\<Diagram\>\"", "]"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[443]:=",
 CellID->327940550,ExpressionUUID->"14a05579-494f-7348-941f-b16ce63cafd8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Second",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": ",
 StyleBox["Cost function ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[LeftAngleBracket]", " ", 
    RowBox[{"H", " ", 
     RowBox[{"(", "\[Theta]", ")"}]}], "  ", "\[RightAngleBracket]"}], 
   TraditionalForm]],
  FontSlant->"Italic",ExpressionUUID->"2525167b-5889-d943-bd13-d2a0dfe6a037"]
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.969364509717462*^9, 3.969364510482308*^9}},
 CellID->469393791,ExpressionUUID->"4e401af5-c557-3c49-ade4-8449a5e1e2e1"],

Cell["\<\
Obtain the QuantumState from the circuit and define the bra and ket for the \
cost function:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954856207319763*^9, 3.9548562152169*^9}, {
  3.954856256818725*^9, 3.9548562607452083`*^9}},
 CellID->205971699,ExpressionUUID->"76368604-706b-7e43-a958-f48fe7b1e7b9"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{"\[Phi]"},
    "Ket"], "=", 
   RowBox[{"HEAnsatz", "[", "]"}]}], ";", 
  RowBox[{
   TemplateBox[{"\[Phi]"},
    "Bra"], "=", 
   SuperscriptBox[
    TemplateBox[{"\[Phi]"},
     "Ket"], "\[Dagger]"]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[445]:=",
 CellID->328105733,ExpressionUUID->"1c404900-3083-0548-838c-b36f30b25bb0"],

Cell["\<\
Compute the energy expectation value symbolically. Simplifying and replacing \
fixed values gives the optimizer access to exact gradients\[LongDash]an advantage \
over shot-noise-limited quantum hardware:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9548562170163193`*^9},
 CellID->113392639,ExpressionUUID->"d897d309-58e2-794e-bfa0-583bf2f48d12"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"energy", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    TemplateBox[{"\[Phi]"},
     "Bra"], "@", 
    RowBox[{"H2", "@", 
     TemplateBox[{"\[Phi]"},
      "Ket"]}]}]}], " ", ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[446]:=",
 CellID->808065639,ExpressionUUID->"ece6bf55-c70c-3a49-b861-0d569943ff94"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"values", "=", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\[Alpha]", "->", "0.4"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "->", "0.2"}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"costH2", "[", 
   RowBox[{
   "\[Theta]1_", ",", "\[Theta]2_", ",", "\[Theta]3_", ",", "\[Theta]4_"}], 
   "]"}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"FullSimplify", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"\"\<Scalar\>\"", "//", "energy"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
       "\[Theta]1", ",", "\[Theta]2", ",", "\[Theta]3", ",", "\[Theta]4"}], 
       "}"}], "\[Element]", "Reals"}]}], "]"}], "/.", "values"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[447]:=",
 CellID->209058165,ExpressionUUID->"9f54bbe4-8a7f-7944-b0ae-576f39ec642f"],

Cell["\<\
The cost function is nontrivial, but symbolic computation gives exact \
gradients, significantly aiding the optimization.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9548562796121025`*^9},
 CellID->153787752,ExpressionUUID->"0b229897-4565-e244-9d7c-6cfc9928f22c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Third",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ": ",
 StyleBox["Optimization",
  FontSlant->"Italic"]
}], "Item",
 CellID->491752659,ExpressionUUID->"1cf9eb6c-5523-2744-9b3e-02ad652c3f7f"],

Cell["\<\
Minimize the cost function over the circuit parameters:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9548562858717575`*^9, 3.9548564122471027`*^9},
 CellID->215673107,ExpressionUUID->"16b2da0e-4f5b-544d-92dd-6a82644ea125"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"resultH2", "=", 
  RowBox[{"NMinimize", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"costH2", "[", 
     RowBox[{
     "\[Theta]1", ",", "\[Theta]2", ",", "\[Theta]3", ",", "\[Theta]4"}], 
     "]"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
     "\[Theta]1", ",", "\[Theta]2", ",", "\[Theta]3", ",", "\[Theta]4"}], 
     "}"}]}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[450]:=",
 CellID->16534878,ExpressionUUID->"34907543-9f6e-5146-88c0-7af96a748718"],

Cell["\<\
The minimum energy is approximately -0.824, obtained at the optimal \
parameters.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954856414761009*^9},
 CellID->440034854,ExpressionUUID->"47e31258-65a6-b041-8be6-ebf35b444a2b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"paramH2", "=", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Last", "[", "resultH2", "]"}], "//", "Association"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[465]:=",
 CellID->415405277,ExpressionUUID->"f976e6be-9828-ab49-8395-87625faa9536"],

Cell["\<\
With four parameters, we fix two at their optimal values and plot the cost \
function over the remaining two to visualize the landscape:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954856633710869*^9, 3.954856641182932*^9}},
 CellID->35994608,ExpressionUUID->"8c709990-9558-014e-8de7-151c5abf9599"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Using a ",
 StyleBox["ContourPlot",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " to visualize the two-dimensional slice:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.9548566429087734`*^9},
 CellID->91006298,ExpressionUUID->"1d2625c1-9d1d-5343-bfcb-7430674e41de"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ContourPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"costH2", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", "\[Theta]2", ",", 
     RowBox[{"paramH2", "[", "\[Theta]3", "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"paramH2", "[", "\[Theta]4", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Pi]"}], "/", "2"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]2", ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Pi]"}], "/", "2"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"FrameLabel", "->", "Automatic"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[469]:=",
 CellID->113139777,ExpressionUUID->"4ee5ae9a-7c11-824f-a789-90e6a50e0122"],

Cell["\<\
Lighter regions correspond to higher energies; blue regions mark the cost \
function minima.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.954856670567131*^9, {3.969364534239406*^9, 3.969364534484151*^9}},
 CellID->524878244,ExpressionUUID->"27e0e546-91f0-f14c-9fcc-76cadf38f062"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ContourPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"costH2", "[", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", 
     RowBox[{"paramH2", "[", "\[Theta]2", "]"}], ",", "\[Theta]3", ",", 
     RowBox[{"paramH2", "[", "\[Theta]4", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]1", ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Pi]"}], "/", "2"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]3", ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Pi]"}], "/", "2"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"FrameLabel", "->", "Automatic"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[474]:=",
 CellID->50851894,ExpressionUUID->"b8ef02a9-c19e-9249-b70d-8cb1bbb73f76"],

Cell["\<\
The optimizer converges toward the blue region. The landscape reveals \
whether the algorithm\[CloseCurlyQuote]s success depends on the initial point\[LongDash]a \
general concern for variational quantum algorithms.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548566832962027`*^9, 3.954856685374569*^9}, {
  3.954856715748808*^9, 3.954856716129202*^9}},
 CellID->124686437,ExpressionUUID->"969e5ee0-3848-924f-895e-a111693690e1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"ContourPlot", "[", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"costH2", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"paramH2", "[", "\[Theta]1", "]"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"paramH2", "[", "\[Theta]2", "]"}], ",", "\[Theta]3", ",", 
     "\[Theta]4"}], "]"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]3", ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Pi]"}], "/", "2"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]}], "}"}], ",", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"\[Theta]4", ",", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", "\[Pi]"}], "/", "2"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"\[Pi]", "/", "2"}]}], "}"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[473]:=",
 CellID->259270631,ExpressionUUID->"f492f20e-4fff-d640-b141-2c4b52c501e6"],

Cell["\<\
The periodic structure of the landscape\[LongDash]a direct consequence of \
the sin and cos dependence from rotation gates\[LongDash]means multiple local \
minima exist. Initialization strategies matter.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954856749915249*^9},
 CellID->52758102,ExpressionUUID->"7ecc35aa-b25d-1340-b410-ec251dbd98ae"],

Cell["Example from  https://arxiv.org/pdf/1909.05074v1", "Text",
 TextAlignment->Right,
 CellID->894092569,ExpressionUUID->"f3fa265c-32fa-c74a-8107-3ce7d7226abe"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Trihydrogen cation ", "Subsubsection",
 CellID->444348876,ExpressionUUID->"f23f3be8-1068-8140-b5c9-4f7591b52d8a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For a more realistic system, consider the trihydrogen cation ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox[
    SubscriptBox["H", "3"], "+"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e46f8311-2dc5-f84d-9ee2-8b7fcc01e661"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548569243686075`*^9, 3.9548569386687975`*^9}},
 CellID->100364925,ExpressionUUID->"fb6229fb-0fc7-3c43-bafe-9ce8840956c7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We use ",
 StyleBox["PennyLane",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to obtain the molecular Hamiltonian. This requires six qubits to encode \
the molecular spin-orbitals."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.954856948478969*^9, {3.9548570052089043`*^9, 3.9548570062248282`*^9}},
 CellID->173863102,ExpressionUUID->"4576a5bd-b3c6-6742-a4ff-064069649256"],

Cell["\<\
Specify the atomic symbols and coordinates:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954857009439262*^9, 3.9548570390136576`*^9}},
 CellID->206748299,ExpressionUUID->"97218c1b-448c-8548-8a53-f66ba0842081"],

Cell["\<\
import pennylane as qml
from pennylane import numpy as np

symbols = [\"H\", \"H\", \"H\"]
coordinates = np.array([0.028, 0.054, 0.0, 0.986, 1.610, 0.0, 1.855, 0.002, \
0.0])

# Building the molecular hamiltonian for the trihydrogen cation
hamiltonian, qubits = qml.qchem.molecular_hamiltonian(symbols, coordinates, \
charge=1)

qml.matrix(hamiltonian)\
\>", "ExternalLanguage",
 CellLabel->"In[4]:=",
 CellID->217440002,ExpressionUUID->"68745fdd-3592-3a4b-84a4-dc873dc368a9"],

Cell["\<\
Alternatively, import the pre-computed Hamiltonian directly:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548573029739437`*^9, 3.954857320479757*^9}, 
   3.9548573945563717`*^9},
 CellID->76421448,ExpressionUUID->"fca03910-8d8a-fa4e-88eb-965186ecfdc2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Import", "[", "\"\<https://wolfr.am/1uXbew3vg\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9548573245243807`*^9, 3.9548573439938083`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[95]:=",
 CellID->131699643,ExpressionUUID->"6535a5bc-6294-e648-b086-c8a714922633"],

Cell["\<\
Convert the NumericArray into a QuantumOperator:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954857019715816*^9, 3.954857551518808*^9},
 CellID->69433221,ExpressionUUID->"72f8ad83-c230-b641-b2ad-d9ff8cd81eba"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"H3", "=", 
  RowBox[{"QuantumOperator", "[", 
   RowBox[{"%", "//", "Normal"}], "]"}]}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[96]:=",
 CellID->284824327,ExpressionUUID->"be8428db-a3d4-444e-9274-8b6bb2c97939"],

Cell["\<\
With no prior knowledge of the molecular structure, a reasonable starting \
point is a layered ansatz: RY rotations on all qubits, followed by a chain \
of CNOT gates for entanglement, then another layer of rotations.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954857563855234*^9, 3.95485756858173*^9}},
 CellID->8750445,ExpressionUUID->"c0c93192-c687-644a-814e-dd9ecd149bb2"],

Cell["\<\
This is a 12-parameter circuit. The entanglement layer creates \
nearest-neighbor correlations:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954857577426756*^9},
 CellID->30758363,ExpressionUUID->"c841af98-c36e-8141-9650-1fc9d71e06dd"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"param", "=", 
   RowBox[{"GenerateParameters", "[", 
    RowBox[{"6", ",", "2"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"basicMixAnsatz", "=", 
   RowBox[{"QuantumCircuitOperator", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"ParametrizedLayer", "[", 
        RowBox[{"\"\<RY\>\"", ",", 
         RowBox[{"Range", "[", 
          RowBox[{"1", ",", "6"}], "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       RowBox[{"EntanglementLayer", "[", 
        RowBox[{"\"\<CNOT\>\"", ",", 
         RowBox[{"Range", "[", "6", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
       "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\"\<Barrier\>\"", ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       RowBox[{"ParametrizedLayer", "[", 
        RowBox[{"\"\<RY\>\"", ",", 
         RowBox[{"Range", "[", 
          RowBox[{"7", ",", "12"}], "]"}]}], "]"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"\"\<Parameters\>\"", "->", "param"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    "]"}]}], ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[99]:=",
 CellID->306474706,ExpressionUUID->"2b61214e-b200-1d4a-96d5-45ecd0856ce0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To learn how to construct layered circuits using ",
 StyleBox["ParametrizedLayer",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["EntanglementLayer ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "please refer to the ",
 ButtonBox["Quantum Optimization documentation",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/\
Wolfram/QuantumFramework/tutorial/QuantumOptimization.html"], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/Wolfram/\
QuantumFramework/tutorial/QuantumOptimization.html"],
 ". "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954857870157612*^9, 3.954857940032591*^9}, {
   3.95485797138414*^9, 3.954857973057079*^9}, 3.95485803283514*^9},
 CellID->48120710,ExpressionUUID->"c1db807d-af93-7849-83d7-4d11c8e5e466"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"basicMixAnsatz", "[", 
  RowBox[{"\"\<Diagram\>\"", ",", 
   RowBox[{"ImageSize", "->", "Full"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[101]:=",
 CellID->819013637,ExpressionUUID->"6c2901a0-fab8-f047-8708-d96479c7fd3c"],

Cell["\<\
For six qubits, the symbolic cost function becomes unwieldy. We switch to \
numerical evaluation:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954858121631717*^9, 3.9548581380388365`*^9}},
 CellID->192960307,ExpressionUUID->"919c5a05-56c3-7046-861a-92f0c5a861f0"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"stateAnsatz", "=", 
   RowBox[{"basicMixAnsatz", "[", "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[9]:=",
 CellID->265460279,ExpressionUUID->"1a3192b9-4558-fb45-86fb-468b00155100"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"matrixH3", "=", 
   RowBox[{"H3", "[", "\"\<Matrix\>\"", "]"}]}], ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[10]:=",
 CellID->650495659,ExpressionUUID->"64115b23-c8cd-c44e-a7ec-903ca24419c6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Define the numerical cost function: replace parameters with real numbers, \
compute the state vector, and evaluate the expectation value of ",
 StyleBox["H",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.954858139828533*^9, 3.954858154884317*^9}},
 CellID->126637731,ExpressionUUID->"27c0c06b-8d11-e843-9518-a94bfbcf46dc"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"ClearAll", "[", "meanEnergy", "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"meanEnergy", "[", 
   RowBox[{"values_", ",", "H_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{"Module", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"ket", ",", "bra", ",", "state"}], "}"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"state", "=", 
      RowBox[{"stateAnsatz", "[", 
       RowBox[{"AssociationThread", "[", 
        RowBox[{"param", ",", "values"}], "]"}], "]"}]}], ";", 
     "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"ket", "=", 
      RowBox[{"state", "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", "]"}]}], ";", 
     "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"bra", "=", 
      RowBox[{
       SuperscriptBox["state", "\[Dagger]"], "[", "\"\<StateVector\>\"", 
       "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"Re", "[", 
      RowBox[{"bra", ".", "H", ".", "ket"}], "]"}]}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]",
    "]"}]}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[11]:=",
 CellID->25205220,ExpressionUUID->"37bcadaa-9c88-d447-a6e9-765bafc7d0da"],

Cell["\<\
Apply a classical optimizer from a physically motivated initial guess:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954858176554216*^9},
 CellID->5660859,ExpressionUUID->"4adc0ac5-16ad-9a4e-8b50-29c4e2fc3703"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"init", "=", 
   RowBox[{"Thread", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"param", ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"\[Pi]", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", 
        FractionBox["\[Pi]", "2"], ",", "\[Pi]", ",", "0", ",", "0", ",", "0",
         ",", "0", ",", "\[Pi]", ",", "0"}], "}"}]}], "}"}], "]"}]}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[13]:=",
 CellID->342067610,ExpressionUUID->"274f05f4-c24a-8e46-a2b1-d975190b1e5a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"FindMinimum", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"meanEnergy", "[", 
     RowBox[{"param", ",", "matrixH3"}], "]"}], ",", "init"}], "]"}], "//", 
  "Quiet"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[14]:=",
 CellID->63487005,ExpressionUUID->"cc85221f-b643-084f-bc85-5045cf39d50b"],

Cell["\<\
To obtain the molecular geometry, one would parametrize the nuclear \
positions and minimize the energy over both circuit parameters and nuclear \
coordinates\[LongDash]a double optimization loop.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.954858184846155*^9},
 CellID->673989219,ExpressionUUID->"ebc87789-dbd4-4b48-baa0-7afa7bd2f93e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 InterpretationBox["Exercises",
  $Line = 0; Null]], "ExerciseSection",
 CellID->59205783,ExpressionUUID->"b80aedf5-01e7-476b-8e1c-54bdbbc49590"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "The following code computes the Hamiltonian for the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["H", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fea3324b-f9c3-4e98-88c0-6941d2930ba6"],
 " molecule. Calculate the ground-state energy using VQE and compare with \
exact diagonalization. (You can import the Hamiltonian from: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"Import", "[", "\"\<https://wolfr.am/1tP2IKEfw\>\"", "]"}]], "Input",
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.950873444880039*^9, 3.9508734465745773`*^9}, {
   3.9508735232931137`*^9, 3.9508735282047825`*^9}, {3.950873590166807*^9, 
   3.95087359198958*^9}},ExpressionUUID->
  "ed8a6b46-590b-4f66-a7e0-c77784744dde"],
 ")"
}], "Exercise",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.969464177372849*^9, {3.969464240292028*^9, 3.969464246180132*^9}},
 CellID->786666320,ExpressionUUID->"65e597df-3491-4e75-b7e6-f1d9f3556a62"],

Cell[BoxData[Cell["\<\
import pennylane as qml
from pennylane import numpy as np

symbols = [\"H\", \"H\"]
coordinates = np.array([[0.0, 0.0, -0.6614], [0.0, 0.0, 0.6614]])

# Building the molecular hamiltonian 
hamiltonian, qubits = qml.qchem.molecular_hamiltonian(symbols, coordinates)

qml.matrix(hamiltonian)\
\>", "ExternalLanguage",
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.950618311790642*^9, 3.95061833989876*^9}, {
    3.95061857368421*^9, 3.950618574929794*^9}, 3.95061861674616*^9},
  ExpressionUUID->"2f804dee-85f5-48df-9f6d-6dabc831ccf0"]], "Input",
 TaggingRules-><|
  "ExternalEvaluateData" -> <|
    "System" -> "Python", "SessionID" -> "default-python-session", 
     "Evaluator" -> Automatic|>|>,
 CellEvaluationLanguage->"Python",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.969464191038649*^9, 3.96946419256717*^9}},
 CellID->727810441,ExpressionUUID->"bb6d0073-27f5-4599-8146-a8f3da63cced"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
